The paper deals with the complexity of index sets for properties of normal finite predicate logic programs, which is a topic in logic and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses constructions of recursive functions and primitive recursive trees, which are topics in computer science theory, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with stable models, which is a concept in logic programming, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible sub-category.
